NAME
       shell - a simple shell program

SYNOPSIS
       shell [OPTION]... [ARGUMENT]...

DESCRIPTION
       The shell program is a simple command-line interface that
       allows users to execute various commands and perform basic
       file operations. It provides a basic interactive environment.

OPTIONS
       None currently supported.

USAGE
       To use the shell, simply type commands and press Enter.
       Available commands include:

       - echo MESSAGE   Print the given message to the console.

       - cat FILENAME   Display the content of a file.

       - cls            Clear the terminal screen.

       - ls             List files and directories in the current directory.

       - rm FILENAME    Remove a file from the current directory.

       - exit           Exit the shell.

       - cd DIRECTORY   Change the current working directory.

       - pwd            Print the current working directory.

       - touch FILENAME Create a new empty file.

       - term           Set the terminal state (e.g., position and colors).

       - write MESSAGE  Write a message to a file.

COMMAND ARGUMENTS
       The shell accepts various command arguments as needed.

EXAMPLES
       - To print a message: shell echo "Hello, world!"

       - To display the content of a file: shell cat example.txt

       - To clear the terminal screen: shell cls

       - To list files in the current directory: shell ls

       - To remove a file: shell rm file.txt

       - To exit the shell: shell exit

       - To change the directory: shell cd /path/to/directory

       - To display the current working directory: shell pwd

       - To create a new file: shell touch newfile.txt

       - To set terminal state: shell term

       - To write to a file: shell write "Some text" to file.txt

